This class is an advanced individualized study in Latin for students enrolled in the Post-Baccalaureate Program in Classical Studies. &#8232;&#8232;
Most students found this to be a great class, as one student stated “this is a fantastic post-baccalaureate level course, combining an emphasis on the finer points of Latin syntax with well-paced discussion of material.” There were some complaints that some of the topics were too easy for a 400-level class, but most students felt they did learn a lot throughout the semester. Many students were disappointed that the course only met once a week because they enjoyed it so much. &#8232;&#8232;
Students raved about Professor Damon, explaining that she is “very knowledgeable and explains new concepts well.” Others felt Professor Damon is “one of the foremost authorities in the field” and appreciated her accessibility to students. &#8232;&#8232;
This class was highly recommended for major students only and most agreed that this would not be a good course for non-Classical Studies majors. A co-requisite for this course is enrollment in CLST402. Permission of the instructor is required to take this class.
